<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134077>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Dorsal and ventral view of Stigmatonotum macronotum sp. nov.A – holotype, male, dorsal view; B – paratype, male, ventral view; C–D – paratype, female (C – dorsal view; D – ventral view). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134077/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134079>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Male genitalia of Stigmatonotum macronotum sp.nov.A – pygophore, dorsal view; B–E – left paramere, four different aspects. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134079/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134081>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Male and female genitalia of Stigmatonotum macronotum sp. nov.A–C – phallus (A – dorsal view, B – ventral view, C – lateral view); D – endophallic reservoir and holding sclerite, lateral view; E – endophallic reservoir, dorsal view; F – holding sclerite; G – spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134081/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134083>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Habitats of Stigmatonotum macronotum sp. nov. A – Ôtaki-machi, Ôtadai, the collecting site of the holotype specimen of H. macronotum sp. nov.; B – Kamogawa-shi, Yomogi, Goudai-rindô, University of Tokyo Chiba forest, the collecting site of paratype specimens of S. macronotum sp. nov.; C–D – Carex multifolia Ohwi, from which holotype specimen of S. macronotum sp. nov. was collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134083/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134085>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Distribution of Stigmatonotum macronotum sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134085/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

